Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-delta (LSM) nanocatalyst-decorated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 (ESB) cathodes for IT-SOFCs were developed via an infiltration technique.
Titulo: Enhancing performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ-infiltrated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 cathodes via controlling wettability and catalyst loading of the precursor solution for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Using different amounts of Triton-X 100 significantly changed the wettability of the LSM precursor solution, thus affecting final characteristics of the LSM nanoparticles.
Titulo: Enhancing performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ-infiltrated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 cathodes via controlling wettability and catalyst loading of the precursor solution for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The best electrochemical performance was obtained at a 1:1 ratio of LSM and Triton-X 100.
Titulo: Enhancing performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ-infiltrated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 cathodes via controlling wettability and catalyst loading of the precursor solution for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Furthermore, tuning the LSM concentration tailored the size and porosity of LSM nanocatalysts.
Titulo: Enhancing performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ-infiltrated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 cathodes via controlling wettability and catalyst loading of the precursor solution for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The ASR of the optimized LSM-infiltrated ESB cathode on GDC electrolyte was as low as 0.16 Omega-cm(2) at 650 degrees C, the lowest ASR among reported LSM-stabilized bismuth oxide cathodes fabricated by the infiltration method.
Titulo: Enhancing performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ-infiltrated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 cathodes via controlling wettability and catalyst loading of the precursor solution for IT-SOFCs
